    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The technique of visually representing sets of facts or statistics collected for reference and analysis in graphical or schematic form. Formats used in data visualization typically include tables, charts and graphs, but may take a variety of pictographic forms. Data visualization increasingly involves digital rendering or processes, but pre- and co-exists with purely analog means of representation.</Note_Text>
